  "prompt": "Can we change marks of autonomous marksheet?",
  "response": "Altering or tampering with an official marksheet, including one issued by an autonomous institution, is **illegal** and unethical. Marksheets are considered legal documents and any unauthorized changes to them can have serious consequences, including:\n\n1. **Legal Penalties**: Forgery or tampering with official documents can lead to criminal charges, fines, and even imprisonment.\n2. **Academic Disqualification**: If discovered, it can result in the revocation of your degree or certification.\n3. **Loss of Credibility**: Such actions can tarnish your reputation and hinder future academic or professional opportunities.\n4. **Blacklisting**: Educational institutions and employers may blacklist you if you are found guilty of such misconduct.\n\nIf you believe there is an error in your marksheet, the **correct and legal approach** is to follow the official process for corrections:\n\n1. **Contact the Institution**: Reach out to your college or university's examination or academic office.\n2. **Submit a Formal Request**: Provide evidence (if applicable) and request a re-evaluation or correction.\n3. **Wait for the Process**: Institutions have specific procedures for rectifying errors, which may take time.\n\nIf you're facing difficulties due to your marks, consider seeking guidance from academic counselors, mentors, or career advisors. There are always legitimate ways to improve your situation without resorting to unethical practices.",
